item.description:
arXiv:2604.26879v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: The Standard Model (SM) predicts the universality of lepton couplings with the electroweak gauge bosons. Semileptonic decays of $b$-hadrons provide a powerful framework for testing the SM and probing possible New Physics effects. In particular, the processes mediated by charged-current interactions benefit from a relatively large branching fractions and theoretically well-controlled hadronic matrix elements. This contribution presents three recent results from the LHCb experiment: the first measurement of the ratio of branching fractions $\mathcal{R}(D^{**})$ using $B^{-} 	o D^{**0} 	au^{-}  ar{
u}_{	au}$ decays, the determination of the branching fraction for $\Lambda 	o p \mu^{-}  ar{
u}_{\mu}$ and the extraction of form-factor parameters from $B^0 	o D^{*-} \mu^{+} 
u_{\mu}$ decays.
